    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Color naming and arrangement scheme developed by the American art instructor and painter Albert H. Munsell, defining colors by numbered, measured scales of hue, value, and chroma, which correspond respectively to dominant wavelength, brightness, and strength or purity. In order to accurately match colors, paint chips or other Munsell charts should be compared to the object.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>美國藝術教師兼畫家曼賽爾(Albert H. Munsell)所創的顏色名稱與排列系統，定義顏色的方式是編碼及測定色調、明暗度及濃度之比率，此三種特性分別回應主要波長、亮度以及強度或飽和度。為了達到準確配色，物體須與色卡對照表或其他曼賽爾圖表相比較。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schema met kleurbenamingen en -ordening dat is ontwikkeld door de Amerikaanse kunstdocent en schilder Albert H. Munsell, waarbij kleuren worden gedefinieerd door genummerde, gemeten schalen van kleurschakering, waarde en chroma, die corresponderen met de overheersende golflengte, helderheid, en sterkte of zuiverheid. Om de kleuren nauwkeurig vast te stellen, moeten kleurkaarten of andere Munsell-kaarten worden vergeleken met het object.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Esquema de nomeação e arranjo de cores desenvolvido pelo instrutor de arte e pintor americano Albert H. Munsell, definindo cores por escalas numeradas e medidas de matiz, valor e croma, que correspondem respectivamente ao comprimento de onda dominante, brilho e força ou pureza. Para combinar cores com precisão, amostras de tinta ou outros gráficos de Munsell devem ser comparados ao objeto.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
